½ tsp salt","½ tsp ground black pepper","500 g water","150 g hot smoked salmon, cut into pieces or flaked"]}],"id":"r150447","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-tMfgYTKT-hA\/XZafyXEz_MI\/AAAAAAAAgyE\/aoEAzp1YDi8m8UtWduNOuptq180tmWGTgCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_w4aBRFWdE5HkXENj.png","title":"Soufflé omelette with hot smoked salmon","publishedAt":"2018-04-02T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"20.5 g","fat":"29.4 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"1.3 g","calories":"1466 kJ \/ 349 kcal"},"usefulItems":"jug, serving plate, sealable container, baking paper, bowl, refrigerator","hintsAndTricks":["You can use a variety of greens in this recipe. Try replacing the kale with spinach, or the parsley with basil.","To save time, you can place both egg whites and yolks into mixing bowl together. However, the omelette will not be as fluffy.","Kewpie mayonnaise can be stored in the refrigerator for up to 3 days."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","25m","4 portions"]}